\textsc{Exercise 5:} Mean or Median, standard deviation, IQR, 5-number summary or Range? For each of the following data scenarios determine which summary statistics are most appropriate to provide a numerical summary of the data?
First consider what data values are plausible and whether plotting these data values in a histogram would yield a more symmetric or a more skewed distribution.\\

\blue{Note that the correct choice depends on the shape of the distribution! For skewed distributions the five-number summary, IQR and median are typically the better choices. For symmetric distributions the mean and the standard deviation (variance) are more optimal.}
\begin{enumerate}
\item[a.] number of songs downloaded to a student's iTunes library for all students in Stat 226
\item[b.] prices of the books on someone's Amazon wish list for young professionals
\item[c.] number of calls handled daily by a corporate call center Mondays through Fridays
\item[d.] number of calls handled daily by a corporate call center weekdays and weekends
\item[e.] salaries at a large manufacturing company
\end{enumerate}


